    "actions_taken": [
      "CCS evacuated and transported to onshore medical facility",
      "Corneal laceration surgery performed",
      "BSEE onsite investigation conducted on 26-SEP-2024",
      "Witness interviews and reenactment performed"
    ],
    "summary": "On 21-SEP-2024 at 1630 hours, a contract construction supervisor (CCS) sustained a corneal laceration to his right eye while learning to use banding material for heliport skirting fence repairs. The CCS was holding a spool of banding material with approximately 2 feet extending when the band clamp buckle slipped off the material, causing the extended section to spring forward, strike and knock off the CCS's safety glasses, and lacerate the cornea. The CCS required surgery.",
